  "name": "Contemptor Osiron Dreadnought",
  "titles": "Contemptor-Osiron Dreadnought",
  "lore": "For many decades, the arts by which the powers of a psyker could be maintained medically into the half-life of Dreadnought internment eluded the Legiones Astartes. It was not until Magnus himself was focused on the issue that a solution, albeit a difficult one, was created. The use of a crowning psychometric barrier lattice for the living brain of the mortally wounded psyker was his answer, a device he named the ‘osiron’. Using principles few even among the Imperium’s foremost psi-arcanists understood, the Thousand Sons began fitting it to the highly adaptable Contemptor Dreadnought chassis with startlingly powerful results.",
